MyCanopy L1 Technical Overview: The chain operates on a proof-of-work consensus mechanism with adjustable difficulty. Each block stores a list of transactions, a timestamp, and a cryptographic hash of the previous block, ensuring immutability and integrity. The codebase is open-source and written in Python 3.10+, with no external dependencies. Transaction finality is achieved once a block is successfully mined and appended to the chain. Future iterations will explore proof-of-stake migration and smart contract support within the Canopy ecosystem
